Every time I listen to this song, I think about my now graduated friends that left me behind after 3 years of me knowing them.

Here's the story:

It all started when me and the friend I now have on discord met each other when I was a freshman in highschool, in the first year, me, him and another friend of his played Yu-Gi-Oh Nexus together. After that year, we had to same class again, but this time, he and more of his friends played SSBU (Super Smash Bros Ultimate for those who don't know) together, I was intrigued by their skill and I joined them, from what I distinctively remember, a few weeks later. That's when the friend I have on discord become my SSBU tag team partner, I played Simon, he played Richtor, I played Lucina, he played Marth, HECK, we've done double Ganondorf and so much more. That is when I truly felt a connection between us. In my junior and his senior year, which was last year, we still played SSBU, and I never thought I would build a new connection between me, him and his friends. When they had to leave 2 weeks before graduation during our yearly senior walkout, I was crying tears of emotion, knowing they were gonna be gone when they graduated 2 weeks from that day. 2 weeks later, I went to their graduation to help National Honors Society with passing out programs, not only that, I wanted to support my friends all the way through the program, best of all, they DID NOT know I was there. At the end, I never had a final encounter with those friends to say a final farewell..... but there was something coming from a friend I had never had before...... The friend on discord sent me this exact message, "Thank you for everything! You're an amazing friend!" That is where I CRIED tears of emotion, because I have never had a friend that was THAT supportive to me, EVER. That was the last I have heard from him or the others......That is how those 3 years (2020-2023) were some of the best years of my highschool life.ğŸ˜­
